{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"find .claude/plans/loloop -maxdepth 1 -type f -printf '%T@ %p\\\\n' | sort -nr | head -8 | cut -d' ' -f2- | xargs -r -I{} sh -c 'echo \\\"--- \"'$1\"; sed -n \"1,160p\" \"$1\"'\"' sh {}\"","aggregated_output":"--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-loop-stop-summary.md\n# Evolution Note — Loop Stop Summary\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on tracks after the core roadmap milestones\n- Bounded target: stop the current daemon cleanly and record a durable handoff summary\n\n## Completed\n\n- Stopped the running `codex-loop` daemon intentionally.\n- Confirmed the daemon is no longer running and the tmux-backed loop session is no longer active.\n- Reviewed the latest loop state and last message to capture where the automation actually ended.\n- Recorded the final loop landing point for future re-entry.\n\n## What This Loop Batch Achieved\n\n- Completed the `task-plans/cma-codex-communication-optimization-task-plan.md` track.\n  - `sendPrompt` optimistic queued state\n  - `auto-continue` optimistic queued feedback\n  - lighter Codex tab link-state synchronization\n  - reduced full refresh / full rerender churn for smaller actions\n- Advanced the `prompt-rule-memo` work and produced multiple evolution notes around prompt/rule/memo card identity and drawer / running-board shortcuts.\n- Re-entered `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md` and finished a bounded audit slice.\n  - Result: the repo still lacks a minimal explicit coordination vocabulary.\n  - Recommended next concrete step: add the smallest possible `ownership / handoff / waiting` state vocabulary before any broader multi-agent UI work.\n\n## Final State At Stop\n\n- Daemon state: stopped intentionally\n- Last automation thread: `019d8b1e-53fa-7162-9931-73aec8b60078`\n- Last completed tick:\n  - log: `.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260415_004118.log`\n  - message: `.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260415_004118_last_message.txt`\n- Current active task track at stop:\n  - `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md`\n- Current bounded slice at stop:\n  - introduce one minimal coordination-state vocabulary for thread ownership, handoff, and waiting\n\n## Operational Notes\n\n- The daemon had been restarted successfully with a `3 min` interval before this manual stop.\n- This stop is not a failure signal; it is a deliberate checkpoint and handoff boundary.\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Resume from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`.\n- Keep the next step narrowly scoped to `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md`.\n- Do not open broader multi-agent workflow UI yet.\n- First land the minimal coordination-state vocabulary, then reassess whether a dedicated coordination surface is justified.\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-codex-multi-agent-reentry-audit.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Re-entered the codex-multi-agent-coordination track and normalized its task-plan into active checkbox form.\n- Confirmed the repo currently has no explicit coordination model for ownership, handoff, or waiting between threads.\n- Isolated the first bounded slice: introduce one minimal coordination-state vocabulary before building larger coordination UI.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: introduce one minimal coordination-state vocabulary for thread ownership, handoff, and waiting\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Patch only the minimal coordination-state vocabulary\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-exit-review.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Reviewed `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md` after the final card-identity patch.\n- Confirmed the track can close cleanly: card types, source integration, and workflow integration are all now complete.\n- Moved the handoff to `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md` for the next re-entry audit.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track transition after `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: close the prompt-rule-memo track and hand off to the next roadmap track\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Start with a re-entry audit for `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md`\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-card-identity.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Made prompt/rule/memo card identity explicit in the memory panel section copy and card labels.\n- Memory cards now present `Prompt Card`, `Rule Card`, and `Memo Card` as first-class types instead of generic kind labels.\n- Closed the last remaining Task 1 gap, so the prompt-rule-memo task-plan is now marked complete.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: make prompt/rule/memo card identity explicit in the memory panel labels and copy\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Do one exit review for `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-task1-audit.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Audited the remaining Task 1 card-type gap after source integration and workflow integration closed first.\n- Confirmed prompt/rule/memo cards already have distinct shells and color treatment, but their identity labels are still generic and the panel copy is still future-tense.\n- Isolated the smallest remaining slice: make the card identities explicit in the memory panel labels and copy.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: make prompt/rule/memo card identity explicit in the memory panel labels and copy\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Patch only the explicit card-identity gap\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-task3-review.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Reviewed Task 3 after drawer shortcuts landed.\n- Confirmed workflow integration can close: spotlight, running board, and drawer now all expose prompt/rule/memo context beside active work.\n- Moved the handoff back to Task 1 because card-type work is the only unchecked area left in this track.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: close Task 3 and hand off to Task 1 audit\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Start with the first bounded Task 1 card-type audit\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-drawer-shortcuts.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Added the existing prompt/rule/memo shortcut row to the thread drawer actions area when the drawer is in its normal action state.\n- Active work now keeps the same memory context across spotlight, running board, and drawer surfaces.\n- Closed the remaining Task 3 slice for surfacing the right memory context beside active work.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: add a bounded prompt/rule/memo shortcut row to the thread drawer\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Do one Task 3 review\n--- .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-prompt-rule-memo-task3-second-audit.md\n## What Changed\n\n- Audited the remaining Task 3 memory-context gap after running-board shortcuts landed.\n- Confirmed spotlight and main running board now expose prompt/rule/memo references, but the thread drawer still does not.\n- Isolated the smallest remaining slice: add a bounded memory shortcut row to the drawer actions area.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Active plan: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- Bounded target: add a bounded prompt/rule/memo shortcut row to the thread drawer\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n- Follow `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- Patch only the drawer memory-context gap\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
